# Chronos Vault - Time-Locked STX Escrow Smart Contract

A comprehensive and secure smart contract system for creating time-locked STX vaults on the Stacks blockchain. Perfect for savings goals, vesting schedules, delayed payments, and secure escrow services.

##  Features
### Core Functionality
- **Time-Locked Vaults**: Create secure vaults with customizable lock periods
- **Multi-Vault Management**: Each user can manage up to 100 vaults simultaneously  
- **Flexible Withdrawals**: Support for both complete and partial withdrawals
- **Portfolio Tracking**: Comprehensive user portfolio management and analytics
- **Activity Logging**: Complete audit trail for all vault operations

### Security Features
- **Access Control**: Vault owners have exclusive access to their funds
- **Emergency Pause**: Contract-wide pause functionality for security incidents
- **Input Validation**: Comprehensive validation of all user inputs
- **Time-Lock Enforcement**: Strict enforcement of lock periods
- **Balance Verification**: Multi-layer balance and authorization checks

### Economic Features
- **Service Fees**: Sustainable 1 STX creation fee model
- **Minimum Lock Period**: 24-hour minimum lock period (144 blocks)
- **Gas Optimization**: Efficient data structures and operations
- **Scalability**: Support for high-volume vault operations

##  Contract Specifications
### Constants & Limits
| Parameter | Value | Description |
|-----------|-------|-------------|
| Maximum Vaults per User | 100 | Vault limit per account |
| Minimum Lock Duration | 144 blocks | ~24 hours at 10 min/block |
| Vault Creation Fee | 1,000,000 µSTX | 1 STX service fee |
| Maximum Vault ID | 999,999,999 | Upper limit for vault identifiers |
| Description Max Length | 50 characters | Vault label character limit |

### Error Codes
| Code | Error | Description |
|------|-------|-------------|
| 1001 | ERR-UNAUTHORIZED-ACCESS-DENIED | User lacks required permissions |
| 1002 | ERR-VAULT-NOT-FOUND-IN-SYSTEM | Vault ID doesn't exist |
| 1003 | ERR-VAULT-STILL-TIME-LOCKED | Lock period hasn't expired |
| 1004 | ERR-INSUFFICIENT-STX-BALANCE | Insufficient STX balance |
| 1005 | ERR-INVALID-DEPOSIT-AMOUNT | Invalid deposit amount (≤0) |
| 1006 | ERR-INVALID-LOCK-DURATION | Lock duration below minimum |
| 1007 | ERR-VAULT-CREATION-LIMIT-EXCEEDED | Too many vaults for user |
| 1008 | ERR-ZERO-BALANCE-OPERATION | Operation on empty vault |
| 1009 | ERR-WITHDRAWAL-EXCEEDS-BALANCE | Withdrawal > vault balance |
| 1010 | ERR-INVALID-VAULT-IDENTIFIER | Invalid vault ID |
| 1011 | ERR-INVALID-STRING-INPUT | Invalid string input |
| 1012 | ERR-CONTRACT-PAUSED | Contract in emergency pause |
| 1013 | ERR-VAULT-LIMIT-EXCEEDED | System vault limit exceeded |
| 1014 | ERR-ACTIVITY-LOG-CREATION-FAILED | Failed to log activity |

##  Usage Guide
### Creating a Vault

```clarity
;; Create a vault with 10 STX locked for 1000 blocks
(contract-call? .chronos-vault create-time-locked-vault 
  u10000000      ;; 10 STX in µSTX
  u1000          ;; 1000 blocks lock duration
  "Savings Goal" ;; Vault description
)
```

### Adding Funds to Existing Vault

```clarity
;; Add 5 STX to vault #1
(contract-call? .chronos-vault add-funds-to-vault 
  u1        ;; Vault ID
  u5000000  ;; 5 STX in µSTX
)
```

### Withdrawing Funds (After Lock Expires)

```clarity
;; Withdraw complete balance from vault #1
(contract-call? .chronos-vault withdraw-complete-balance u1)

;; Withdraw 3 STX from vault #1
(contract-call? .chronos-vault withdraw-partial-amount 
  u1        ;; Vault ID
  u3000000  ;; 3 STX in µSTX
)
```

### Updating Vault Description

```clarity
;; Update vault label
(contract-call? .chronos-vault update-vault-label 
  u1                    ;; Vault ID
  "Emergency Fund 2024" ;; New description
)
```

##  Query Functions
### Vault Information

```clarity
;; Get vault details
(contract-call? .chronos-vault get-vault-details u1)

;; Check if vault is unlocked
(contract-call? .chronos-vault is-vault-unlocked u1)

;; Get remaining lock time in blocks
(contract-call? .chronos-vault get-remaining-lock-time u1)
```

### User Portfolio

```clarity
;; Get user's complete portfolio
(contract-call? .chronos-vault get-user-portfolio 'SP1234...)

;; Get total locked STX for user
(contract-call? .chronos-vault get-user-total-locked-stx 'SP1234...)
```

### Contract Analytics

```clarity
;; Get contract-wide statistics
(contract-call? .chronos-vault get-contract-analytics)

;; Get contract configuration
(contract-call? .chronos-vault get-contract-config)
```

### Activity Logging

```clarity
;; Get specific vault activity
(contract-call? .chronos-vault get-vault-activity u1 u1)

;; Get next activity index
(contract-call? .chronos-vault get-vault-next-activity-index u1)
```

##  Data Structures
### Vault Record
```clarity
{
  vault-owner: principal,           ;; Vault owner address
  locked-amount: uint,              ;; STX amount locked (µSTX)
  unlock-block-height: uint,        ;; Block when funds unlock
  creation-block-height: uint,      ;; Creation timestamp
  last-activity-block: uint,        ;; Last activity timestamp
  vault-label: (string-ascii 50),   ;; User-defined description
  vault-status: (string-ascii 20)   ;; "ACTIVE" or "EMPTIED"
}
```

### User Portfolio
```clarity
{
  owned-vault-ids: (list 100 uint), ;; List of owned vault IDs
  total-locked-amount: uint,        ;; Total STX locked by user
  active-vault-count: uint,         ;; Number of active vaults
  last-portfolio-update: uint       ;; Last update timestamp
}
```

### Activity Log Entry
```clarity
{
  action-type: (string-ascii 30),        ;; Type of action performed
  transaction-amount: uint,              ;; Amount involved in µSTX
  block-timestamp: uint,                 ;; Block height of action
  initiator-address: principal,          ;; Address that initiated action
  additional-context: (string-ascii 100) ;; Additional context info
}
```

##  Administrative Functions
### Emergency Pause (Deployer Only)
```clarity
;; Toggle contract pause state
(contract-call? .chronos-vault toggle-contract-pause)
```